                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Charleston So. Ca.</placeName>\n                                        <date>April 21<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> 1849</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">Dr &amp; Reverend Sir,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(7)\">I should have answered your several<lb/>\n                                        communications long ere this, but business both private\n                                        &amp; public<lb/> prevented me from doing myself this\n                                        pleasure. Now you would<lb/> justly say, that any man can\n                                        write a few lines, however his<lb/> time may be monopolized\n                                        by his avocation, and, with much pro=<lb/>priety you could\n                                        instance it in your own person, whose time<lb/> being very\n                                        limited, is yet able to carry on a correspondence<lb/>\n                                        almost over the whole Union. I would answer you in few<lb/>\n                                        words <add>לאו כל אדם זוכה</add>!! Besides my principal\n                                        reason for not having been more<lb/> prompt is, that I\n                                        determined never to appear before you empty handed,<lb/>\n                                        viz, without contributing something to the Occident, and\n                                        thus I offer<lb/> you the enclosed trifle which you may\n                                        insert in your invaluable journal<lb/> if you find it worthy\n                                        to have a place therein, and good enough to<lb/> stand the\n                                        scrutiny of the <sic>criticising</sic> public. As regards\n                                        the<lb/> proposed convention, I hope to give you soon more\n                                        fully my opinion<lb/> on it, for I can assure that I\n                                        anticipated such results. <persName>Mr Hart</persName><lb/>\n                                        has no doubt acquainted you with the fact, that the\n                                        Congregation<lb/> Shearit Israel will not join the\n                                        Convention. You are doubtlessly dis<lb/>appointed, and I am\n                                        really sorry that your zeal and honest<lb/> endeavors in the\n                                        good cause are so little appreciated by our<lb/> brethern,\n                                        and the, so much cherished, hope of affecting a Union<lb/>\n                                        of <placeName>Israel</placeName> in the <placeName>United\n                                                  States</placeName> will have to be relinquished\n                                        for the<lb/> present</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37d2qq43/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
