                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37d2qq43/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>motives. Selfishness, lukewarmness, and the natural\n                                        disposition<lb/> of our people to oppose are the stumbling\n                                        blocks in our<lb/> way, but we must nevertheless keep on and\n                                        steadily pursue<lb/> the true course, and we cannot fail.\n                                        There are little news<lb/> here which interest you, except\n                                        that next <sic>thursday</sic> a concert<lb/> is to be given\n                                        in behalf our congregation may the Lord<lb/> grant them\n                                        success for the congregation is much in need of<lb/>\n                                        pecuniary aid. By the by, I was informed yesterday that<lb/>\n                                        <persName>D Landsberg</persName>, who was expected to\n                                        succeed <persName>Mr Poznanski</persName>, re=<lb/>fuses\n                                        coming, for several reasons, the principal of which<lb/>\n                                        are, that he expected $500.00 for travelling expenses, and\n                                        they<lb/> only sent him $200.00 and again, he only wishes to\n                                        be minis=<lb/>ter and not Chazan. There is besides a great\n                                        deal of contention<lb/> amongst them, and <persName>Mr\n                                                  P.</persName> has lost ground even amongst\n                                        his<lb/> own party. Hoping that this may find you in the\n                                        enjoyment<lb/> of the best of health, and fervently wishing\n                                        that the Lord<lb/> may prolong your days for the Benefit of\n                                        our Brethern and the cause.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(6)\">I remain</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(7)\">Most sincerely</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(7)\">Yr friend and colleague</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">I Rosenfeld</persName>\n                              </p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37d2qq43/canvas/p3"
                }
